    "(8) implies our D 2 -equivariant GNN needs to maintain a node feature matrix H ðtÞ g for every G-transformation of the current input, and these views are recombined by invoking g G on all pairs related together by applying a transformation h. Note that all reflections are self-inverses, hence, in D 2, g = g À1.",
    "It is worth noting that both the frame averaging in Eq.",
    "(6) and group convolution in Eq.",
    "(8) are similar in spirit to data augmentation.",
